The two-day conference was held via video and leaders from 111 countries around the world were invited to attend, including the leader of Taiwan, but leaders from China and Russia were not invited."
On the eve of the summit, China and Russia criticized the US over its own problems with democracy, claiming that the US was not qualified to host such a summit.
There are also voices of criticism both internationally and in the US, such as criticism of leaders invited to the conference, including some leaders with authoritarian tendencies, such as the leaders of the Philippines, Poland, and Brazil, and some people doubt the true intention of the Biden government to organize this summit for democracy, not for geopolitical purposes.
