A statement from China's Foreign Ministry on Saturday said, "Today's American-style democracy is showing signs of sickness, with problems such as money politics, identity politics, party opposition, political polarization, social division, racial conflict, and wealth differentiation becoming more and more intense." American democracy is a "rich man's game" built on a capital base.
US President Biden stated in his speech, "As leaders of the government, we have a responsibility to listen to our citizens, reinforce the safeguards of democracy, drive reforms, achieve transparent accountability, and better resist the forces of authoritarianism and those who blatantly pursue power before the public interest."
He emphasized that democracy is not a matter of course, "We must constantly renew it among every generation, in my view, this is the decisive challenge of our era."
Biden also said that global democracy and human rights "need fighters to defend them at a time of persistent and worrying challenges."
The American side promised to launch a one-year action after this democracy summit, including an initiative of $424.4 million to strengthen democracy around the world and support independent media.
The United States hopes that all countries will make concrete public commitments to improve their democratic systems before the planned physical democracy summit to be held at the end of 2022.
Biden said, "Let us all implement our commitments and report on the progress we have made next year."